post_text: Thank you to our amazing administration, teachers and staff for another great year! Pictured are the employees that enjoyed the WFEE’s year end celebration in their honor!
text: Thank you to our amazing administration, teachers and staff for another great year! Pictured are the employees that enjoyed the WFEE’s year end celebration in their honor!

post_text:
Thank you to Mrs. Annette Rau for sharing a prime example of what your donations to the WFEE are providing to our students and community:

The Foundation’s grant provided more than just material for our group, it opened up learning opportunities, made connections possible, helped create a community and taught empathy for these kids.

We were able to accomplish some really amazing goals this spring! With my help, guidance and the support of adult volunteers, 22 students and 7 teachers collaborated to create quilts for two very special children in our district battling cancer!

post_text:
It’s that time of year again! The sun is out and the weather is amazing, which means you are itching to get on the golf course.

Please consider joining the WFEE in support of our local schools and students! The foundation is a not-for-profit that was established to receive gifts, bequests and grants to compliment, enrich and enhance the educational opportunities and experiences for the students of WCUSD#5. All proceeds go towards scholarships, purchasing or enhancing equipment, field trip transportation and other educational opportunities.

Thank you in advance for any consideration in the way of a hole sponsor and/or team entry!

post_text: Thursday is our annual golf tournament at the Waterloo Country Club! We couldn't be more excited about the expected weather and turnout! Thank you for the support to everyone who has registered and to our wonderful hole sponsors. Even if you are not playing please come and enter to win an Amazon Echo or $250 Visa Cash Cards. $5/Ticket or $10/3. We hope to see you there!

This is our only fundraiser each year, therefore, your support would be greatly appreciated in the form of a team registration or hole sponsor. We are a 501(c)(3) organization that has supported our students and teachers this year in some of the following ways:

Young Adult Book Club
Fine Motor Objects
Science Materials
Post Prom
Reading Pens
Chrome Books
Field Trip Transportation

Thank you in advance for any consideration!

WFEE recently had the privilege of providing donations to selected teachers for needed supplies, equipment and/or funding. Congrats to this year's recipients!

Pictured Left to Right: Teacher Representative Laura Lenhardt, Teachers Angie Augustine, Amy Wagonknecht, Jamie Holtman, Carrie Rieken, Board Member Martha Ward, Teacher Carrie Munsell, and Board Members Jamie Nobbe & Dan Lane.

Teachers Not Pictured Receiving Donations: Kara Lavoie and Andy Mayer
